        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 5 at 8:58AM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 857 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Mechanicsville, moving northwest at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, pea size hail, and torrential
rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ashland, Randolph Macon College, Mechanicsville, Hanover, Dawn, Glen
Allen, Kings Dominion, Montpelier, Studley, Wyndham, Laurel,
Golansville, Gum Tree, Elmont, Gilman, Solomons Store, Atlee,
Ashcake, Oliver, and Hanover Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
